related.title: Texas' size, defense overwhelms Navy
related.headline: Texas' size, defense overwhelms Navy

article.headline: Jackson's double-double leads Longhorns
article.linkText: No. 2 Texas nearly doubles up Montana in Classic final
article.story:
HONOLULU (AP) -- Texas made quick work of Montana's zone defense.

Tiffany Jackson had 18 points and 14 rebounds in the No. 2
Longhorns' victory over Montana on Sunday night in the championship
game of the Rainbow Wahine Classic.

The Longhorns (6-0) broke down overmatched Montana's zone
defense and shot 55.7 percent (34-of-61) from the field.

"They are so active and quick, we thought that would help, but
they didn't just fire 3s, they got it inside," Montana coach Robin
Selvig said. "They were patient and smart.

"We didn't go man soon enough, but it probably wouldn't make a
difference the way the game went because they have so many weapons
and their big kids are so strong."

Tournament MVP Heather Schreiber added 15 points for Texas,
Jamie Carey had 12 and Coco Reed 11.

"I thought they played the hardest they could from beginning to
end considering it was our fifth game in seven days," Texas coach
Jody Conradt said.

Julie Deming and Hollie Tyler scored 12 points each for Montana
(3-1), which shot just 31 percent (18-of-58), including 2-of-16
from 3-point range.

"We tried to put pressure on them, make them start their
offense farther away from the basket and just be active and have
lots of energy on the defensive end," Conradt said.

In earlier games, Hartford beat Virginia 74-63 for third place,
No. 21 Arizona defeated Hawaii 66-57 for fifth, and Syracuse was a
60-46 winner over Navy for seventh.
